dom-pushevent-constructor.name: PushEvent
dom-pushevent-constructor.summary: The PushEvent() constructor creates a new PushEvent object. Note that this constructor is exposed only to a service worker context.
dom-pushevent-constructor.title: PushEvent()

dom-pushevent-data.name: data
dom-pushevent-data.summary: The data read-only property of the PushEvent interface returns a reference to a PushMessageData object containing data sent to the PushSubscription.
dom-pushevent-data.title: PushEvent.data

pushevent-interface.name: PushEvent
pushevent-interface.summary: The PushEvent interface of the Push API represents a push message that has been received. This event is sent to the global scope of a ServiceWorker. It contains the information sent from an application server to a PushSubscription.
pushevent-interface.title: PushEvent

dom-pushmanager-getsubscription.name: getSubscription
dom-pushmanager-getsubscription.summary: The PushManager.getSubscription() method of the PushManager interface retrieves an existing push subscription.
dom-pushmanager-getsubscription.title: PushManager.getSubscription()

dom-pushmanager-permissionstate.name: permissionState
dom-pushmanager-permissionstate.summary: The permissionState() method of the PushManager interface returns a Promise that resolves to a string indicating the permission state of the push manager. Possible values are 'prompt', 'denied', or 'granted'.
dom-pushmanager-permissionstate.title: PushManager.permissionState()

dom-pushmanager-subscribe.name: subscribe
dom-pushmanager-subscribe.summary: The subscribe() method of the PushManager interface subscribes to a push service.

chrome.notes: The options parameter with a applicationServerKey value is required.

firefox.notes: From Firefox 72 onwards, can only be called in response to a user gesture such as a click event.

firefox_android.notes: From Firefox Android 79 onwards, can only be called in response to a user gesture such as a click event.

edge_blink.notes: The options parameter with a applicationServerKey value is required.

dom-pushmanager-subscribe.title: PushManager.subscribe()

dom-pushmanager-supportedcontentencoding.name: supportedContentEncodings
dom-pushmanager-supportedcontentencoding.summary: The supportedContentEncodings read-only property of the PushManager interface returns an array of supported content codings that can be used to encrypt the payload of a push message.
dom-pushmanager-supportedcontentencoding.title: PushManager.supportedContentEncodings

pushmanager-interface.name: PushManager
pushmanager-interface.summary: The PushManager interface of the Push API provides a way to receive notifications from third-party servers as well as request URLs for push notifications.
pushmanager-interface.title: PushManager

dom-pushmessagedata-arraybuffer.name: arrayBuffer
dom-pushmessagedata-arraybuffer.summary: The arrayBuffer() method of the PushMessageData interface extracts push message data as an ArrayBuffer object.
dom-pushmessagedata-arraybuffer.title: PushMessageData.arrayBuffer()

dom-pushmessagedata-blob.name: blob
dom-pushmessagedata-blob.summary: The blob() method of the PushMessageData interface extracts push message data as a Blob object.
dom-pushmessagedata-blob.title: PushMessageData.blob()

dom-pushmessagedata-json.name: json
dom-pushmessagedata-json.summary: The json() method of the PushMessageData interface extracts push message data by parsing it as a JSON string and returning the result.
dom-pushmessagedata-json.title: PushMessageData.json()

dom-pushmessagedata-text.name: text
dom-pushmessagedata-text.summary: The text() method of the PushMessageData interface extracts push message data as a plain text string.
dom-pushmessagedata-text.title: PushMessageData.text()

pushmessagedata-interface.name: PushMessageData
pushmessagedata-interface.summary: The PushMessageData interface of the Push API provides methods which let you retrieve the push data sent by a server in various formats.
pushmessagedata-interface.title: PushMessageData

dom-pushsubscription-endpoint.name: endpoint
dom-pushsubscription-endpoint.summary: The endpoint read-only property of the PushSubscription interface returns a string containing the endpoint associated with the push subscription.
dom-pushsubscription-endpoint.title: PushSubscription.endpoint

dom-pushsubscription-expirationtime.name: expirationTime
dom-pushsubscription-expirationtime.summary: The expirationTime read-only property of the PushSubscription interface returns a DOMHighResTimeStamp of the subscription expiration time associated with the push subscription, if there is one, or null otherwise.
dom-pushsubscription-expirationtime.title: PushSubscription.expirationTime

dom-pushsubscription-getkey.name: getKey
dom-pushsubscription-getkey.summary: The getKey() method of the PushSubscription interface returns an ArrayBuffer representing a client public key, which can then be sent to a server and used in encrypting push message data.
dom-pushsubscription-getkey.title: PushSubscription.getKey()

dom-pushsubscription-options.name: options
dom-pushsubscription-options.summary: The options read-only property of the PushSubscription interface is an object containing the options used to create the subscription.
dom-pushsubscription-options.title: PushSubscription.options

dom-pushsubscription-tojson.name: toJSON
dom-pushsubscription-tojson.summary: The toJSON() method of the PushSubscription interface is a standard serializer: it returns a JSON representation of the subscription properties, providing a useful shortcut.
dom-pushsubscription-tojson.title: PushSubscription.toJSON()

dom-pushsubscription-unsubscribe.name: unsubscribe
dom-pushsubscription-unsubscribe.summary: The unsubscribe() method of the PushSubscription interface returns a Promise that resolves to a boolean value when the current subscription is successfully unsubscribed.
dom-pushsubscription-unsubscribe.title: PushSubscription.unsubscribe()

pushsubscription-interface.name: PushSubscription
pushsubscription-interface.summary: The PushSubscription interface of the Push API provides a subscription's URL endpoint and allows unsubscribing from a push service.
pushsubscription-interface.title: PushSubscription

dom-pushsubscriptionoptions-applications.name: applicationServerKey
dom-pushsubscriptionoptions-applications.summary: The applicationServerKey read-only property of the PushSubscriptionOptions interface contains the public key used by the push server.
dom-pushsubscriptionoptions-applications.title: PushSubscriptionOptions.applicationServerKey

dom-pushsubscriptionoptions-uservisibleo.name: userVisibleOnly
dom-pushsubscriptionoptions-uservisibleo.summary: The userVisibleOnly read-only property of the PushSubscriptionOptions interface indicates if the returned push subscription will only be used for messages whose effect is made visible to the user.
dom-pushsubscriptionoptions-uservisibleo.title: PushSubscriptionOptions.userVisibleOnly

dom-pushsubscriptionoptions.name: PushSubscriptionOptions
dom-pushsubscriptionoptions.summary: The PushSubscriptionOptions interface of the Push API represents the options associated with a push subscription.
dom-pushsubscriptionoptions.title: PushSubscriptionOptions

extensions-to-the-serviceworkerglobalsco.name: push_event
extensions-to-the-serviceworkerglobalsco.summary: The push event is sent to a service worker's global scope (represented by the ServiceWorkerGlobalScope interface) when the service worker has received a push message.
extensions-to-the-serviceworkerglobalsco.title: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope: push event

dom-serviceworkerglobalscope-onpush.name: push_event
dom-serviceworkerglobalscope-onpush.summary: The push event is sent to a service worker's global scope (represented by the ServiceWorkerGlobalScope interface) when the service worker has received a push message.
dom-serviceworkerglobalscope-onpush.title: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope: push event

the-pushsubscriptionchange-event.name: pushsubscriptionchange_event
the-pushsubscriptionchange-event.summary: The pushsubscriptionchange event is sent to the global scope of a ServiceWorker to indicate a change in push subscription that was triggered outside the application's control.
the-pushsubscriptionchange-event.title: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope: pushsubscriptionchange event

dom-serviceworkerglobalscope-onpushsubsc.name: pushsubscriptionchange_event
dom-serviceworkerglobalscope-onpushsubsc.summary: The pushsubscriptionchange event is sent to the global scope of a ServiceWorker to indicate a change in push subscription that was triggered outside the application's control.
dom-serviceworkerglobalscope-onpushsubsc.title: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope: pushsubscriptionchange event

dom-serviceworkerregistration-pushmanage.name: pushManager
dom-serviceworkerregistration-pushmanage.summary: The pushManager property of the ServiceWorkerRegistration interface returns a reference to the PushManager interface for managing push subscriptions; this includes support for subscribing, getting an active subscription, and accessing push permission status.
dom-serviceworkerregistration-pushmanage.title: ServiceWorkerRegistration.pushManager

extensions-to-the-serviceworkerregistrat.name: ServiceWorkerRegistration
extensions-to-the-serviceworkerregistrat.summary: The ServiceWorkerRegistration interface of the Service Worker API represents the service worker registration. You register a service worker to control one or more pages that share the same origin.
extensions-to-the-serviceworkerregistrat.title: ServiceWorkerRegistration
